news.title: Nashik civic body's property tax up 22% in current financial year
news.para: The civic body’s collection of property tax was severely affected during the previous fiscal due to the Covid pandemic. But various measures taken by the NMC — like amnesty scheme and issuance of warrants for confiscation of properties — led to adding Rs 24 core in the coffers of the civic body.

news.title: FIR against 51 for carving out illegal colonies in Sultanpur & Farrukhnagar
news.para: On the complaint of department of town and country planning (DTCP), 10 FIRs have been lodged against the offenders who were developing 10 illegal colonies ranging from two to eight acres on prime agricultural land.

news.title: Noida: Residential projects will get OCs after environmental experts' nod
news.para: In fact, the Noida Authority has already shortlisted two firms for hiring environmental experts for overseeing compliance with the NGT norms.

news.title: Errors in property IDs? Walk into Gurugram civic body camps to fix them
news.para: While some residents complained that their properties are shown in their neighbour’s name, some said their house numbers in the new property ID are wrong. Some residents also claimed that they were unable to make the corrections online, and would therefore have to visit the MCG office to rectify the mistakes.

news.title: Cement prices rise just as demand grows
news.para: According to various brokerage reports, based on dealer interactions, the pan India average cement price rose by over 10% to Rs 395 per 50 kg bag as of March 22, 2022, on a month-on-month basis. It grew by 11% based on the year-on-year comparison.

news.title: Gurugram: Architects, engineers could face FIRs for building flaws
news.para: The move comes against the backdrop of the vertical collapse of living rooms at Chintels Paradiso that claimed two lives on February 10. Residents there had for long raised questions on the structural safety of buildings.

news.title: Raj Shivganga buyers move Bombay HC to restrain lender from taking flats' possession
news.para: Directors Jayesh Rami, Rajesh Savla and Ashwin Mistry of Raj Arcades and Enclaves Pvt Ltd (RAEL) had mortgaged 23 flats in July 2017 against a Rs 12-crore loan for the project, misrepresenting them as unsold flats (see timeline graphic).

news.title: Flat cancelled over instalment? Buyer won't get booking amount
news.para: It has also been decided that if a builder cancels the allotment of a buyer over non-payment of several instalments, it has to refund only the principal amount after deducting the money paid during booking a flat, that too after the unit has been resold or the project is completed.

news.title: Bombay HC tells Orbit Ventures' partners to repay Axis Finance funds or face imprisonment
news.para: While accepting the duo’s request to suspend the order, the court said on Wednesday that the order sentencing them would come automatically into force if they again failed to make the payment in tranches by the end of September, as promised under the revised terms.

news.title: HeidelbergCement sees energy cost hit due to Ukraine crisis
news.para: Like steel and chemicals, cement production is among the more energy-intense manufacturing processes, making power costs a key factor in determining whether companies can hit their profit goals.

news.title: U.S. new home sales drop further as mortgages rates rise; prices push higher
news.para: Economists saw reduced affordability curbing activity in the near-term, but expected the new housing market to plod along this year given pent-up demand, a record low inventory of previously owned homes and strong wage gains.

news.title: MLAs from rural areas to get MHADA houses in Mumbai
news.para: Jitendra Awhad said the legislators who do not have a house in Mumbai, do not represent any constituency in the city and who hail from outside the Mumbai Metropolitan Region will be eligible for this scheme.

news.title: Residents worry over errors in Mangaluru civic body's online property tax data
news.para: “They have entered the name wrong. Correcting it is a nightmare because of queues. Tax paid for previous years do not reflect and trying to upload it is another nightmare,” said a citizen, whose name was misspelt in the online data of properties.

news.title: Reliance Communications resolution professional seeks buyers for non-core assets
news.para: The RP has invited expressions of interest by April 17 for six assets: land in Pune (871.1 sq metres) and Chennai (3.44 acres); offices on Chennai's Haddows Road and Bhubaneswar; and shares of Campion Properties Ltd and Reliance Realty.

news.title: No property tax relief for villages merged with Pune civic body
news.para: "Though not adequate, the PMC has provided facilities in the merged villages. The tax has been increased in phases. It is not appropriate to introduce a reduction," Tanpure said.
